世卫组织称没有证据显示新冠病毒会在夏天消失https://www.thepaper.cn/newsDetail_forward_6378352日内瓦时间 3 月 6 日，世界卫生组织卫生紧急项目执行主任迈克尔·瑞安在「例行记者会」称“我们尚不清楚新冠病毒在不同气候条件下如何活动和表现。
The WHO said there was no evidence that the virus would disappear in the summer at https: / / www.thepper.cn / news Detail _ forward _ 6378352 Geneva time. "We don't know how the new crown virus works and behaves in different climates," Michael Ryan, WHO's Executive Director of Health Emergency Projects, told a regular press conference on March 6.
”他提醒必须假设新冠病毒在夏天仍具有传播能力。
He warned that it must be assumed that the new crown virus would still be able to spread over the summer.
为此，各国必须抓紧行动，而不能指望新冠病毒会像流感病毒一样在夏天自行消失。
To do so, countries must act quickly, and not expect the new cap virus to disappear like the flu virus in the summer.
。
.
港大推测新冠发病死亡率1.4%http://china.caixin.com/2020-03-06/101525048.html3 月 6 日，香港特区政府防疫专家顾问团成员、香港大学李嘉诚医学院院长梁卓伟根据数据建模g的研究结果显示，新冠肺炎的发病死亡率上限为 1.4%，这一比率低于世卫组织给出的 3.4%。
HKU conjectures a new crown morbidity rate of 1.4% http: / / china.caixin.com / 2020-03-06 / 101525048.html. On March 6, a study based on data modeling g by Professor Leung Cheuk-wai, Dean of the Li Ka Shing School of Medicine, The University of Hong Kong, showed that the upper limit was 1.4%.
梁卓伟认为将新冠累计死亡人数除以累计确诊患者总数的方法是错误的。
Mr Leung said it would be wrong to divide the cumulative number of deaths in the new crown by the cumulative total number of patients diagnosed.
“因为分母中有不少为近期确诊病例，他们病程刚刚开始，无法判断之后究竟会康复还是病情恶化而亡，也有许多无症状感染者或未能纳入分母当中”。
"There are many asymptomatic infections or failure to include the denominator because the denominator has a lot of recent confirmed cases and they are just beginning to tell whether they will recover or if their condition deteriorates."
。
.
病毒命名再起争议 12位华人学者发文支持现名http://www.caixin.com/2020-03-06/101524891.html3 月 5 日，国际期刊《柳叶刀》在线发表了美国乔治梅森大学系统生物学教授吴云涛、香港大学李嘉诚医学院教授金冬雁、浙江大学动物科学学院教授黄耀伟等 12 位华人学者撰写的通讯文章，文章称采用“SARS-CoV-2”命名新冠病毒，符合国际病毒分类委员会（ICTV）的命名原则，“是恰当的” 。
The International Journal of Lancet on March 5 published a newsletter by 12 Chinese scholars, including Wu Yuntao, Professor of Systems Biology at George Mason University, Professor Jin Dongyan at Li Ka Shing School of Medicine, University of Hong Kong, and Huang Yawei, professor of animal science at Zhejiang University.
文章认为，SARS-CoV-2 这个命名并不是基于临床症状与SARS类似，而是突出它与SARS 病毒在演化关系上的考虑。
The article argues that the name SARS-CoV-2 is not based on clinical symptoms similar to SARS, but rather highlights its evolutionary relationship with the SARS virus.
。
.
自 2 月 11 日 ICTV 发布病毒名称后，学界一直有争议。
Academics have been debating the name of the virus since its release on Feb. 11.
2月19日，复旦大学病原微生物研究所所长姜世勃、中国疾控中心主任高福、中科院武汉病毒研究所研究员石正丽等在《柳叶刀》上发文称，ICTV为新冠病毒所取的“SARS-CoV-2”有误导性，暗示它会导致SARS或类似疾病。
Speaking in The Lancet on February 19, Jiang Shibo, director of the Institute of Pathogenic Microbiology at Fudan University, Gao Fu, director of the China CDC, and Shi Zhengli, a researcher at the Wuhan Institute of Virus of the Chinese Academy of Sciences, wrote in The Lancet.
他们呼吁将病毒命名为HCoV-19（“2019年人冠状病毒”）。
They called for the virus to be named HCoV-19 ("Human coronavirus 2019").
城市防控。
Urban control.
武汉出院患者隔离日期延长至28天https://www.thepaper.cn/newsDetail_forward_6378558在 3 月 6 日《新闻1+1》栏目中，中央指导组防控组社区防控专家组负责人吴浩称，“武汉出院患者要有 14 天集中隔离观察和 14 天居家医学隔离观察，要经历加起来28天的隔离观察期。
"Wuhan patients discharged from the hospital will have 14 days of intensive quarantine and 14 days of home medical isolation," Wu Hao, head of the group's community prevention and control group, said in the March 6 column of "theepaper.cn / newsDetail _ forward _ 6378558.
”其中，第一个 14 天的集中医学隔离点观察是统一安排，在酒店、学校等地，每50人配备一位医生和护士，隔离期满前需完成两次核酸检测和一次肺部 CT，达到标准且没有呼吸道的症状，才能回到小区开始第二个 14 天隔离。
The first 14 days of intensive medical seclusion are managed in a unified fashion, with one doctor and nurse for every 50 people in hotels, schools, etc., and two nucleic acid tests and one pulmonary CT before the end of isolation, meeting standard and no respiratory symptoms, before returning to the community to begin a second 14-day isolation.
。
