新冠临床试验首次系统回顾，许多实验方法论存在缺陷http://www.caixin.com/2020-03-07/101525326.html上海交通大学第六人民医院朱长太团队联合多机构发文，对中国已注册临床试验进行首次系统的回顾。
The first systematic review of the new crown clinical trials found deficiencies in many experimental methodologies http: / / www.caixin.com / 2020-03-07 / 101525326.html, a joint multi-agency communication by the Zhu Changtai team of the Sixth People's Hospital of Shanghai Jiaotong University, providing the first systematic review of registered clinical trials in China.
这篇文章称各种类型的临床试验秩序混乱且数量激增，由于试验质量差、样本量小、完成时间长，在今后相当长的一段时间内，我们将无法获得可靠、高质量的临床依据。
The article says that all types of clinical trials are disorderly and proliferating, and that because of poor quality, small sample sizes, and long lead times, we will not be able to obtain reliable, high-quality clinical evidence for a long time to come.
。
.
文章从中国临床试验注册中心与美国临床试验数据库筛选了 2 月 9 日及此前的 75 项 COVID-19 已注册临床试验。
The paper screened 75 COVID-19 clinical trials from the Chinese Clinical Trials Registry and the US Clinical Trials Database on Feb. 9 and before.
部分临床试验缺乏科学设计，将导致质量不高。
The lack of scientific design in some clinical trials will result in poor quality.
所有 63 个介入型试验均未澄清失访偏倚，即观察病例退出研究队列，部分介入型试验在随机性上有很高的偏倚风险。
None of the 63 interventional trials clarified the missed bias, that is, the observed cases dropped out of the study cohort, and some of the interventional tests presented a high risk of bias in randomness.
其中，有 17 个试验没有提及随机性，而有 6 个试验被判定为非随机试验；很少有试验进行分布隐藏；只有 9 个试验对参与者、人员和结果评估实施了盲法，以减少试验主观因素的影响。
Of these, 17 did not mention randomness, while 6 were judged to be non-random; few trials were conducted to hide; and only 9 tested blind methods on participants, people and results assessment to reduce the impact of subjective factors in the tests.
。
.
外围影响。
Peripheral effects.
